  "id": "ambition_crushed",
  "title": "When Dreams Die",
  "description": "A goal you've been working toward becomes impossible, and the loss reverberates through everything.",
  "content": "The door slams shut—the opportunity evaporates, the plan collapses, the dream proves unreachable. You'd invested so much: time, energy, hope, identity. You'd let yourself believe this was your path forward, and now there is no path. The specific loss is painful, but worse is the meta-lesson you're drawing: maybe reaching for things only sets you up for disappointment. Maybe ambition itself is the problem.",
